          <div style="border:1px solid #dbeafe;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin:8px 0;">
            <h3 style="margin:0 0 6px 0;color:#1d4ed8;">What is Python?</h3>
            <p style="margin:0;line-height:1.6;">Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language. (Lesson 1: What is Python?) Emphasizes simplicity and readability to make coding easier to learn and faster to develop.</p>
          </div>
        
          <div style="border:1px solid #dbeafe;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin:8px 0;">
            <h3 style="margin:0 0 6px 0;color:#1d4ed8;">Key characteristics</h3>
            <p style="margin:0;line-height:1.6;">High-level: abstracts many low-level details. Interpreted: runs line-by-line without a separate compile step. Readable syntax: designed for clarity and fewer lines of code.</p>
          </div>
        
          <div style="border:1px solid #dbeafe;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin:8px 0;">
            <h3 style="margin:0 0 6px 0;color:#1d4ed8;">Common uses (from the lesson)</h3>
            <p style="margin:0;line-height:1.6;">Web development Data science Artificial intelligence Automation Software development</p>
          </div>
        
          <div style="border:1px solid #dbeafe;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin:8px 0;">
            <h3 style="margin:0 0 6px 0;color:#1d4ed8;">Why learn Python?</h3>
            <p style="margin:0;line-height:1.6;">Low barrier to entry — good for beginners. Widely used across many fields, making skills broadly applicable. Fast development cycle due to simple syntax and interpreted nature.</p>
          </div>
        
          <div style="border:1px solid #dbeafe;border-radius:10px;padding:10px;margin:8px 0;">
            <h3 style="margin:0 0 6px 0;color:#1d4ed8;">Simple example (from the lesson)</h3>
